Class Word

  • java.lang.Object
    • Word
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    TreeComparable

    public class Word
extends java.lang.Object
implements TreeComparable
    This class is used to create a Word object, which holds a word, a word count, and a linked list that holds its line number and position from the getty address. The class implements TreeComparable to define methods for operating, visiting and comparing binary tree.
    Version:
    8/12/19
    Author:
    Jonathan Kohler
